{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e94-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3322"},"text":"§ 3322.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Cost contracts","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e95-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Cost-plus-a-percentage-of-cost System of Contracting Prohibited","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The cost-plus-a-percentage-of-cost system of contracting may not be used.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e96-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Cost-plus-a-fixed-fee Contracts","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The fee for performing a cost-plus-a-fixed-fee contract for experimental, developmental, or research work may not be more than 15 percent of the estimated cost of the contract, not including the fee. The fee for performing a cost-plus-a-fixed-fee contract for architectural or engineering services for a public work or utility plus the cost of those services to the contractor may not be more than 6 percent of the estimated cost of that work or project, not including fees. The fee for performing any other cost-plus-a-fixed-fee contract may not be more than 10 percent of the estimated cost of the contract, not including the fee. Determinations under this subsection of the estimated costs of a contract or project shall be made by the head of the agency at the time the contract is made.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e97-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Advance Notice of Certain Subcontracts.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e98-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Except as provided in paragraph (2), each cost contract and each cost-plus-a-fixed-fee contract shall provide for notice to the agency by the contractor before the making, under the prime contract, of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e99-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/c/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a cost-plus-a-fixed-fee subcontract; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e9a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/c/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a fixed-price subcontract or purchase order involving more than the greater of (i) the simplified acquisition threshold, or (ii) 5 percent of the estimated cost of the prime contract.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e9b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Exception","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Paragraph (1) shall not apply to a prime contract with a contractor that maintains a purchasing system approved by the contracting officer for the contract.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e9c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Limitation on Certain Options.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e9d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Except as provided by paragraph (2), a covered contract shall limit the number of low-rate production lots for any production quantities procured using fixed-priced options under such covered contract to not more than one.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e9e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Waiver.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e9f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/d/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The service acquisition executive of the military department concerned or, in the case of program that is a joint program, the Secretary of Defense may waive the limit required under paragraph (1) with respect to the number of low-rate production lots for a production quantity under a covered contract if such service acquisition executive or the Secretary of Defense, as applicable, determines that such waiver is in the best interest of the Department of Defense.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3ea0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/d/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Delegation limit","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Neither a service acquisition executive nor the Secretary of Defense may delegate the authority under subparagraph (A) to waive the limit required under paragraph (1) below the level of a service acquisition executive.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3ea1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this subsection:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3ea2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/d/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “covered contract” means a cost reimbursement contract for the development of a major system.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3ea3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/d/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “low-rate initial production” has the same meaning as in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s4231"},"text":"section 4231 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3ea4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3322/d/3/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “major system” has the meaning given such term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3041"},"text":"section 3041 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3ea5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added and amended ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXVIII/s1817/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XVIII, § 1817(a)","children":[],"tail":", (c), (e), (f), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4186"},"text":"134 Stat. 4186","children":[],"tail":", 4187; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159/dA/tVIII/s802/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159, div. A, title VIII, § 802(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2024-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2024","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/138/1965"},"text":"138 Stat. 1965","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaa1d3ea6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaa1d3ea7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idaa1d3ea8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For derivation of subsec. (a) of this section, see Codification note related to subsec. (a) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2306"},"text":"section 2306 of this title","children":[],"tail":" set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3321"},"text":"section 3321 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The text of subsec. (d) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2306"},"text":"section 2306 of this title","children":[],"tail":", which was transferred to this section, redesignated as subsec. (b), and amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1817/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1817(e)","children":[],"tail":", (f)(2), was based on "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/131"},"text":"70A Stat. 131","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The text of subsec. (e) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2306"},"text":"section 2306 of this title","children":[],"tail":", which was transferred to this section, redesignated as subsec. (c), and amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1817/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1817(e)","children":[],"tail":", (f)(3), was based on "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/131"},"text":"70A Stat. 131","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/dB/tVII/s2724"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, div. B, title VII, § 2724","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-18"},"text":"July 18, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1193"},"text":"98 Stat. 1193","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/25/tVII/s701/d/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–25, title VII, § 701(d)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-04-06"},"text":"Apr. 6, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/114"},"text":"105 Stat. 114","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/tIV"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, title IV","children":[],"tail":", 4401(c), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3348"},"text":"108 Stat. 3348","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/136/dA/tVIII/s842"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–136, div. A, title VIII, § 842","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-11-24"},"text":"Nov. 24, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/1552"},"text":"117 Stat. 1552","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idaa1d3ea9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2024—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1817/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1817(c)","children":[],"tail":", (f)(1), transferred first sentence of subsec. (a) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3321"},"text":"section 3321 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to this section, designated it as subsec. (a), and inserted heading."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1817/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1817(e)","children":[],"tail":", (f)(2), redesignated subsec. (d) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2306"},"text":"section 2306 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as subsec. (b) of this section and inserted heading."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1817/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1817(e)","children":[],"tail":", (f)(3), redesignated subsec. (e) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2306"},"text":"section 2306 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as subsec. (c) of this section, inserted subsec. and par. headings, and realigned margin of par. (2)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idaa1d3eaa-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idaa1d3eab-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section and amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2022","children":[],"tail":", with additional provisions for delayed implementation and applicability of existing law, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1801/d"},"text":"section 1801(d) of Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date of 2021 Amendment note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3001"},"text":"section 3001 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idaa1d3eac-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Conforming Regulations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159/dA/tVIII/s802/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159, div. A, title VIII, § 802(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2024-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2024","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/138/1965"},"text":"138 Stat. 1965","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/118/159/dA/tVIII/s802/b"},"text":"“Not later than 120 days after the date of the enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2024-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2024","children":[],"tail":"], the Secretary of Defense shall revise the Department of Defense Supplement to the Federal Acquisition Regulation to implement subsection (d) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3322"},"text":"section 3322 of title 10","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, as added by subsection (a) of this section.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
